I pushed north a few times, getting it to (42,10). I did something along the east edge too. Now, I'm here at (42,12). The boulder is at (42,10). Gotta get that thing onto a fountain. I *think* the fountain is at (41, 9). Time to cross-reference the Y=9 row of the map... Yep, there's a fountain at (41,9).

So, the boulder is at (42,10). Can I push it west? Nope, wall at (43,10). I'm at (42,12), so pushing north would put it at (42,9), which isn't a fountain. Wait... no, hold on. Let's look at the rows at Y=9, Y=10, Y=11, and Y=12. Okay, the boulder is *not* blocked by a wall at (42,9). (42,9) is a `.`. The same with (41,10).

Okay, now it's clear: if I push the boulder north to (42,9), I can't push it west because (41,10) is a wall. It's stuck! And if I push it west to (41,10), it's also blocked. So it is stuck from the south!

Wait, am I overlooking something? I'm gonna move east. Row 13 looks promising. Aha! If I go west to (35,13), I can access the left side. Okay, let's explore, or maybe try to move *other* boulders.
